alma_experimentation.title: Add import profile to load Gobi records with purchase order lines

comments.body:
From Brian Harrington:

```
I had been assuming that I would have to write some custom code to load the CPF files, but we have a bigger problem.  Until the agent record improvements in ANW-429 are merged in, the necessary database fields to hold all of the information in your CPF records don't exist in ASpace, and I'm not sure that the extra effort of importing EAC-CPF is worth it if we aren't getting any richer metadata in the authority file.  

Because of this, I think the best bet is to plan on cleaning up the names in the EADs.  Then once the agent record  improvements are in place, you could look at another project to overlay the extra data from the CPF records on top of your existing authorities.
```

dspace-development.title: Test importing the 2019 Mechanical & Aerospace Engineering theses
Indexing is failing for the imported DataSpace dissertations

comments.body:
Indexing is failing using the following JRuby commands:

```
java_import org.dspace.discovery.SolrServiceImpl
index_service = DSpace.getIndexService
item = DSpace.fromString(handle)
index_service = DSpace.getIndexService
index_service.indexContent(DSpace.context, item, true)
index_service.getSolr.commit
```

There is a file-system level permissions issue which is triggering Solr from indexing:
```
Caused by: java.io.FileNotFoundException: /var/cache/tomcat/temp/upload__7e9a8c0d_1735399fe3c__7fff_00042421.tmp (Permission denied)
        at java.io.FileOutputStream.open(Native Method)
        at java.io.FileOutputStream.<init>(FileOutputStream.java:221)
        at java.io.FileOutputStream.<init>(FileOutputStream.java:171)
        at org.apache.commons.io.output.DeferredFileOutputStream.thresholdReached(DeferredFileOutputStream.java:178)
        at org.apache.commons.io.output.ThresholdingOutputStream.checkThreshold(ThresholdingOutputStream.java:224)
        at org.apache.commons.io.output.ThresholdingOutputStream.write(ThresholdingOutputStream.java:128)
        at org.apache.commons.fileupload.util.Streams.copy(Streams.java:101)
        at org.apache.commons.fileupload.util.Streams.copy(Streams.java:64)
        at org.apache.commons.fileupload.FileUploadBase.parseRequest(FileUploadBase.java:362)
```

Manually committing the document update with:

```
index_service.getSolr.commit
```

was necessary, but the Solr indexing is now functioning.
The index has been updated for the September 2019 dissertation imports.
The index has been updated for the June 2020 dissertation imports.

That isn't the case right now. Only the parent "John Foster Dulles Papers" page has the "components" tab where you can navigate all the way down. pulfalight.title: Spin-out indexing into a separate application?

comments.body: Do you have any concerns with there being a disconnect between how a document is converted and how the frontend responds to a certain Solr document? I feel like I've had that happen in some of our other apps before. The only other thing which might be an issue is we wouldn't be able to copy over any specs from Arclight master anymore. Maybe that's okay?

@tpendragon To me, the disconnect between the converted document and frontend behavior with a solr document is the primary argument against doing this. I'm not as concerned about being able to copy/paste specs from Arclight. We don't typically do that in our other blacklight applications.

pulfalight.title: ASpace does not export container locations to EAD

comments.body:
I don't believe having physloc notes in the component is a robust workaround (though it may be the only one), since any given component may have more than one top container, and they could be in different locations. The only way to parse the locations of those containers would therefore be document order.

E.g. 

```
 <c level="file" id="AC112_c00524">
<did>
<unittitle>Quadrangle Club</unittitle>
<unitdate>dates not examined</unitdate>
<container>
<ptr target="AC112_i13"/>
</container>
<container>
<ptr target="AC112_i140"/>
</container>
<container>
<ptr target="AC112_i290"/>
</container>
<physdesc>
<extent type="computed">portion of 3 boxes</extent>
</physdesc>
</did>
</c>
```

would then look like

```
<c id="aspace_AC112_c00524" level="file">
	<did>
		<unittitle>Quadrangle Club</unittitle>
		<unitdate>dates not examined</unitdate>
		<physdesc id="aspace_39e4ffd2012c5e2919042a649cb1e61c">portion of 3
								boxes</physdesc>
		<physloc id="aspace_05d6aa168be9ac7fe6a3a2282edc8dd8">mudd</physloc>
		<physloc id="aspace_660988b002b8f8c075d770c76545a069">mudd</physloc>
		<physloc id="aspace_9c5ec00920b669acf4c0c8f8e97dd64d">mudd</physloc>
		<container id="aspace_99037545665bfdac1f77db57e72880fe"
								label="mixed materials [32101113553455]" type="box">SP13</container>
		<container id="aspace_ec1c5eaec147346b421f34c9de73511a"
								parent="aspace_99037545665bfdac1f77db57e72880fe" type="box"
								>MP156</container>
		<container id="aspace_13c5810b4af2ca9f7ee626964ccd0320"
								parent="aspace_ec1c5eaec147346b421f34c9de73511a" type="box"
								>LP77</container>
		</did>
</c>
```
